{"name": "loldeps", "metadata": {"name": "LOLDeps", "version": "0.0.4", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A tool to find vulnerabilities in packages using native package manager tools such as nuget.", "upload_time": 1734712235}, "documentation": ["# LOLDeps\nLOLDeps stands for Living Off the Land Dependencies, it is a simple tool that uses native package managers to highlight vulnerabilities in your package manifests and alerts you when it finds issues.\n\n```shell\nusage: LOLDeps.py [-h] [--path PATH] [--failure-level FAILURE_LEVEL] [--ado]\n\noptions:\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n  --path PATH           Path to the directory where your code and package manifest is held.\n  --failure-level FAILURE_LEVEL\n                        Provide the risk level that must be failed on. Options: critical, high, moderate\n  --ado                 Choose if you are running in Azure DevOps pipeline.\n```"], "modules": [{"name": "LOLDeps", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "LOLDeps.dependency_checker", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "LOLDeps.dependency_checker.categorise_package_vulnerabilities", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "packages", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "dotnet_vulnerabilities", "type": {"name": "DotNetVulnerabilities", "xref": {"fqname": "LOLDeps.dependency_checker.DotNetVulnerabilities", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "package_type", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "LOLDeps.dependency_checker.check_d